OL,3,CThe loneliness of the long distance
OL,4,Ccyclist
OL,6,FCyclists were told to turn back and
OL,7,Fcomplete the journey back to London
OL,8,Fwhere they would receive their medals
OL,9,Ffor having completed the curtailed
OL,10,Froute.
OL,12,FOne rider though, Ian McBride from New
OL,13,FZealand, had already made it ahead of
OL,14,Fthe storm and was well on his way to
OL,15,Fthe Scottish capital.
OL,17,FHe's now on his way back down south,
OL,18,Fon course to be the only rider to
OL,19,Ffully complete the course as intended.
